P R O J E T. Depuis le début du confinement, on s’est lancé dans des projets de ménage intense et de certains travaux à la maison. Celui-ci en est un...qui trainait depuis des années! Bien heureuse du résultat et ce, avec tout des articles et peinture que nous avions déjà à la maison! C’est notre façon à nous de se changer les idées et de ne pas trop stresser avec ce qui se passe! ••• 🧹••• PROJECT. Since the start of the quarantine, we have started on intense housework projects and some deep cleaning. The laundry room is one of them... that has been hanging around for years! Very happy with the result, with all items and paint we already had at home! It’s our way of not to stress too much about what’s happening right now!

post_content:
View this post on Instagram

After 🖤 vs Before👉 (SWIPE TO SEE our laundry room make over) Let me start by saying that Erick and I live in an older home. We love it for that exact reason. It has character and charm 🏡 But sometimes a little paint and new hardware is the ticket 🎨 This quarantine has got me feeling all the feels, just like you! I am really down for a few days, then lazy, then hungry. You get the picture. But I couldn't walk past this room everyday without seeing so much potential. Plus we are in here a lot! Laundry doesn't do itself. Go figure! 🥴 I started this project on Thursday and I am happily enjoying the fruits of my labor this evening. It's simple, it's not some fancy bells and whistles room, but it is ours to use for now and I'm thrilled with the final look. I don't want to sound obnoxious but I encourage all of us to do something creative during this weird time. Do something productive that you can look back on, smile and feel PROUD. These are trying times mentally, physically and emotionally. But when we let our creative juices flow, you might see that this quarantine doesn't have to be ALL bad. 💯 #homesweethome #homeimprovement #laundryroommakeover #mydecorvibe #beforeandafter #paintingparty #houseproject #diy #peepmypad #progresspicture #lovewhereyoulive #quarantinelife #targetdoesitagain

This @oneroomchallenge space has come a LONG way. We kept the upper cabinets and just updated the hardware. Adding in the pretty tile and repainting made all the difference. We also updated the plumbing, something you can’t see but allowed us to push the washer and dryer back closer to the wall, in a space this tight every inch counts. The ikea base cabinet and back shelf adds much needed storage and functionality. I’ll share the connected half bath soon, its a challenge to take pictures in. I enjoy being in and using this room so much more! Happy hump day, friends! Oh laundry. Even in quarantine it’s one of my least favorite chores 😅. At least we can work on it throughout the day now whenever, and not all on the weekend.
